0s. Probably sensor not responding and last response stuck in logger memory allocation.
0s. Probably sensor not responding and last response stuck in logger memory allocation.
Spikes/constant values. Probably sensor not responding and last response stuck in logger memory allocation.

Odd behavior in RH sensor at power on: Plausibly, when the tower was powered back on after being off, the (heated) RH sensor needed to warm and equillibrate. It seems this equillibration period is 15-30 min and has a characteristic shape: when the tower turns on the RH starts very low, increases very high then falls back to the accurate value. Instead of automating a screening procedure I just mannually screened the RH data.

LWD tracks LWU closely while this is not the case at Met City or ASFS40 (ASFS30 appears to have the same issue). Likely freezing fog on the radiometer dome leading to icing and erroneous measurements.
deployed near ASFS30 but the LWD increased for this period to values near and above LWU, suggesting frozen drizzle or some other icing.
clear signs of icing on the dome compared to ASFS30 and Met City
